name: Banksy 6" Bomb hugger (White) Figure
description:
Bomb Hugger first appeared on the streets of the East End of London which depicts a girl holding a bomb. Apparently, the girl represents purity, where the bomb represents war.

Please note this is not made by banksy but is just a bit of fun and for the price will look great around the house to complement your artwork.

This also comes with paint if you wish to give it your own touch!

name: Banksy 6" Copper (White) Figure
description:
Undoubtedly one of Banksy’s most iconic images, his first commercial print release way back in 2002 and should it need any explanation, it’s a British Policeman giving the bird, which kind of sums up the attitude of the UK establishment

Please note this is not made by banksy but is just a bit of fun and for the price will look great around the house to complement your artwork.

This also comes with paint if you wish to give it your own touch!
